task.summary: Default task
Gave Sensor___Manager classes their own Logging constants
Abstracted out long permissions code with centralized method, renamed all activities to have class prefix Activity
Improved permission handling and moved permissions code into PermissionManager class
Removed all reference to permissions constants from activity classes, making permissions management in other activities very easy (calls to PermissionManager)
Connected activity configure to the data collection service, to user tune the parameters Added button to ActivityMain to navigate to ActivityConfigure
Added star to indicate service connection status, to aid debugging
ActivityMain only stops service if service is not foregrounded
Allowed user to update location update frequency options
Added check for grantResults.length 0 to avoid Index Out of Bounds
Made Default sensor update intervals Constants and a factor of the MIN_TIME of the GPS sensor (can easily remove dependancy in the Constants class if needed)
Moved Location Listener back into DataCollectionService
Added continual polling without location update
More space efficient audio histogram code
Updated to use server at port 80 (default http), defined port explicitly despite being assumed incase future change
Added test implementation of likely places, to find public places they are likely to be at. This will allow the user to select a place name if they know it, if not to enter their own.
Added voluntary crowd observation, currently gets the estimation for your location however does not post it back yet
Test implementation of sending crowd observation, need to abstract away into another service that manages the notifications to the user asking for crowd observations
Added case for user enters invalid number (no number at all)
Implemented replacement launcher activity, still in intermediate stage
Made new ActivityNavigation the default launcher and removed remains of activitymain
Improved Menu Structure
Added barebone fragments
Plugged navigation bar into empty fragment classes
Graphical representation of occupancy in the local area, currently does multiple request, need to adapt API to do the processing and return results in a single request
Updated app to work with bulk occupancy API
Tweaking distance of occupancy estimate polls
activitynavigation parameters into final fields, ready to be abstracted away to a occupancy estimate service
Renamed DataCollectionService to ServiceDataCollection
Refactored json variable names into NavigationContract class
Increased transparency of occupancy indicators overlaying map

Added long press map marker, so user can request occupancy of any location (this part not yet implemented) Cancelled mapPollTimer on app pause Made app zoom to user location on launch Removed default computer science marker Improved handling of crowd occupancy estimation dialogue, if server returns string "null" for no data available
Aligned occupancy poll nodes with map Drawing occupancy with squares Occupancy polling now based on center latlng of mMap viewport
Made squares clickable to get occupancy at that location
Modularised ActivityConfig with a ScrollView > Linear Layout > FrameLayout format Containing each section of settings in an individual FrameLayout, with a Space seperating them
Improved Settings Layout, and simplified underlying layout strucutre
Added code ready for debug squares to show, which aids understanding of underlying map polling Removed message button (fab) from bottom of ActivityNavigation
Removed unneeded time checks in every sensor manager Layed out groundwork to implement SharedPreferences to propagate settings from ActivityConfigure elsewhere
Got Map polling config to update and reload after re-launch too
Service and Map Polling all done with shared preferences and onSharedPreferenceChangeListener
Allowed user to update sensor polling interval
mapPollTimer and cameraCenterTimer log their interval times for quicker debugging
Removed redundant API Test Activity, moved likely place item to the menu rather than navigation drawer
Cancelled the sensor_timer in the service onDestroy method, to prevent the service's children classes working after it has been destroyed (except to complete the remainder of their last request)
Updated graph page intent to new link (without html extension)
Updated graph page intent to new link (without html extension)

Increased stability when permissions are denied Reduced the size of the location polling area for the meantime (local testing purposes) Set opacity of 0 readings to 5, so user can see the area covered Removed (commented out) map long onclick listener Made app revert to FusedLocationApi.getLastLocation if location update isnt available yet on this run
Added check if lastLocation is null even after getLastLocation called, just incase Added layout framework for Going back in occupancy time
Added the ability to look back in time at previous occupancy estimates
Performance testing and use case build
